FT  12 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Higgs &amp; Hill makes Pounds 720,000 purchase
Higgs &amp; Hill has acquired Carter Commercial Developments for Pounds 720,000
plus a profit-related payment from the receiver of Flintclose, a subsidiary
of Speyhawk. Carter specialises in the development of out-of-town retail
sites.
Mr John Theakston, chief executive of Higgs, said the purchase was an
important part of the company's strategy as it came out of recession.
